PERTH (miningweekly.com) &ndash; Uranium miner Energy Resources of Australia (Era) has announced that its CEO and MD Andrea Sutton will resign to take up a position with parent company Rio Tinto. Sutton, who was appointed CEO and MD in 2013, will work with the board to ensure a smooth transition to her successor, Era said on Friday. The timing of Sutton&rsquo;s departure and the appointment of her successor will be announced in due course, the company said, noting that the recruitment for a replacement will start shortly.